article_title: Yankton County Gets Its Own Identifying Logo
article_text:
Yankton, SD

South Dakota's Yankton County is finally getting its own identifiable logo.



The county has never had an official seal, but a new logo has been working its way onto letterhead and the halls of the Yankton County Government Center.



Yankton County Register of Deeds Brian Hunhoff says the process began early this year when he was asked whether the county has an identifying seal at all. He says some individual offices were using elements such as eagles or the Meridian Bridge, but the county had no seal or logo that represented the government as a whole.



Commissioners adopted a committee's design in August.
